entnext-nongraphical-enumeration — ENTNEXT/ENTLAST reach dictionary/xrecord objects
====================================================================================

Status: OPEN, verification BLOCKED on live CAD (schms-data-selection 1.6.8).
Parent: drawing-data-structures-parity / selection-and-snapshot-parity.

Model decision DICT-1 (drawing/source/dictionary.lisp): clautolisp stores
dictionaries and xrecords as handle-bearing objects in the ENTITIES table,
so their ENAMEs feed straight into ENTGET/ENTMOD/ENTDEL with no parallel
code path. A consequence: ENTNEXT/ENTLAST, which walk the entity table in
creation order, can enumerate these non-graphical objects.

On AutoCAD/BricsCAD, dictionaries and xrecords live in the OBJECTS
section, NOT the ENTITIES section, so ENTNEXT/ENTLAST do NOT return them
(they walk model/paper-space graphical entities and their subentities).
SSGET already matches the vendor (graphical-entity-p excludes them).

Question to resolve on a live CAD, then reconcile:
- Does the SCHMS corpus (or any portable probe) rely on ENTNEXT NOT
  returning dictionary/xrecord objects? If yes, filter ENTNEXT/ENTLAST by
  graphical-entity-p too (2-line change, host-entnext/host-entlast in
  entity-api.lisp). If the corpus never observes the difference, document
  the divergence and leave it.

Cheap fix if verification says confine: wrap the host-entnext /
host-entlast candidate test with clautolisp.drawing:graphical-entity-p,
mirroring the ssget scan. Deferred only because it needs a CAD run to
confirm the vendor contract for the exact SCHMS traversal idioms.

Documented in the spec NAMEDOBJDICT *** clautolisp note.
